President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the appointment of Ahmad Salihijo Ahmad as the Managing Director and Chief Executive Officer of Rural Electrification Agency. Ahmad Salihijo, a renewable energy expert holds two masters degree in development studies and project planning and has acquired vast knowledge and experience in power sector development. He is an indigene of Adamawa State. Also appointed are Olaniyi Alaba Netufo as Executive Director, South west and Eddi Mietuade Smith Julius as non-Executive Director, South-South. Tanimu is an Online Editor with Africa's Largest TV Network. Produces when not on Social media.